revisions.rev:
[[Cornwall Council]] in [[England]], [[United Kingdom|UK]], is elected every four years. From 1973 to 2005 elections were for Cornwall [[County Council]], with the first election for the new [[Unitary authority|unitary]] Cornwall Council held in June 2009. This election saw 123 members elected, replacing the previous 82 councillors on Cornwall County Council and the 249 on the six district councils.<ref>[http://www.cornwall.gov.uk/default.aspx?page=17444 Cornwall Council June 2009 Electoral divisions]</ref>

==Political control==
Since 1973 political control of the county council, from 1973 to 2009, and then the unitary council after 2009, has been held by the following parties:<ref name=hung>{{cite news| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/shared/bsp/hi/elections/local_council/09/html/4159.stm | title = Cornwall | accessdate = 2009-11-27 | publisher = ''[[BBC News Online]]'' | date=19 April 2009}}</ref><ref name=gain>{{cite news| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/shared/vote2005/locals/html/3852.stm | title = Local election results: Cornwall | accessdate = 2009-11-27 | publisher = ''[[BBC News Online]]''}}</ref>
